 Wizkid Nigerian Singer, Ayo Balogun Ibrahim, well known as Wizkid has expressed his love for his music career, revealing the other career path he would have taken if he wasn’t into music. In an interview with Naomi Campbell, Wizkid revealed that music changed his life so much that if not for that he would have probably ended up on the streets. He said; “If I wasn’t blessed to be doing music I would have probably been on the streets.
“I am not from a rich family and I wasn’t raised with a silver spoon so I feel I was blessed so I can be a blessing to my family and to those around me.
“I believe if I wasn’t making music I would have been on the streets hustling like every other kid.
”God blessed me with music and it’s safe to say music changed my life. It also changed the life of those I love and care about.” 